Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.79,0:00:02.19,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Here we come!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.42,0:00:04.42,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's time for Inuyasha!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.19,0:00:06.79,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}We're going to gather all\nthe shards of the Sacred Jewel...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.86,0:00:08.92,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}And I'll destroy Naraku\nwith my Tetsusaiga!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.23,0:00:11.43,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}The battle is about to begin\non sacred grounds.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.77,0:00:15.40,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Having increased the power of his giant\nhalberd Banryu with the Shikon Jewel shards,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.47,0:00:18.70,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Bankotsu, the leader of the Band of Seven\nstands ready, awaiting our arrival.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.11,0:00:20.80,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's up to us and Miroku,\NSango, Shippo and Kirara!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.88,0:00:22.87,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Travel back in time\nfor a Feudal Fairy Tale!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.21,0:00:24.18,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Inuyasha!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.12,0:02:13.38,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Father, it hit Hijiri Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.59,0:02:16.06,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Yes. You stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.29,0:02:17.16,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.36,0:02:20.45,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I must check to see that\NSaint Hakushin Temple is safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.67,0:02:35.40,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,This is the staff entrusted to our ancestors\nby the wise one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.74,0:02:37.11,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Take me, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.58,0:02:40.81,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Shintaro, you must go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.95,0:02:41.68,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}But....{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.82,0:02:44.79,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Understand this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.02,0:02:48.75,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,If anything should happen to me,\nas the son of the village headman,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.82,0:02:51.82,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,you are the only one\nwho can protect Hijiri Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.10,0:02:57.83,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Don't worry. I'll be home\nby morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.54,0:03:02.50,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Father....{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.35,0:03:12.97,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.52,0:03:14.81,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Well, Inuyasha?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.39,0:03:18.15,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,This isn't it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.49,0:03:20.46,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,It didn't smell\nlike this marsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.72,0:03:24.72,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was the scent of water\nand flowers that{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.09,0:03:26.65,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}I sensed from Naraku's\ndemon puppet.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.54,0:03:36.83,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,And it was pure like\NMt. Hakurei.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.47,0:03:39.41,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Well then, let's try checking\nother lakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.84,0:03:41.71,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I wonder if Sango and\NKirara are okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.92,0:03:53.82,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Mt. Hakurei!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.93,0:03:57.55,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.30,0:04:05.49,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Kirara, it's painful for you to\ncross the barrier, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.50,0:04:09.87,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I'm {\i1}sorry....{\i0} forcing you like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.18,0:04:15.07,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.08,0:04:16.60,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Sango!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.88,0:04:18.04,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.28,0:04:18.84,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.95,0:04:23.28,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,The barrier around Mt. Hakurei\nis even stronger than before.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.45,0:04:26.39,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,It's impossible to enter\nthrough it then?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.12,0:04:31.08,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I'm sure of it. Naraku has\nbeen close by.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.53,0:04:35.49,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Let's check every waterway\naround the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.27,0:04:46.04,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Please, take me out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.54,0:04:52.54,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,No, you have a duty to take the\nplace of your father as headman.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.81,0:04:55.65,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,We can't place you in\nany danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.95,0:04:58.25,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,But Father has been gone\nfor two weeks!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.69,0:05:00.45,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Something must have happened\non Hijiri Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.09,0:05:04.35,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,But the only ones allowed\non Hijiri Island
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.43,0:05:06.79,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,are the village {\i1}headmen....{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.30,0:05:09.36,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Which means only you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.43,0:05:13.30,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Just give me a boat.\NI'll go alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.67,0:05:19.20,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Your father didn't do anything\nto raise the wrath of the Saint, did he?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.54,0:05:22.48,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,We can't have the village\ncursed, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.78,0:05:25.80,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,My father has lived his whole life\nfulfilling his duties as headman!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.25,0:05:28.77,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,He wouldn't do anything\nlike that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.02,0:05:31.32,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,We'll be punished if\nwe go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.62,0:05:33.55,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Hiriji Island is a sacred place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.82,0:05:36.26,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.03,0:05:41.12,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Did I just hear something\nabout a sacred place?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.56,0:05:43.53,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Will you talk to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.63,0:05:47.53,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Close to the center of this lake
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.84,0:05:50.77,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,is an island which is\nforbidden to common folk.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.91,0:05:55.78,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,The duty of village headman has been\npassed down through my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.84,0:05:57.87,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,And only our men have been\nallowed on the island
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.95,0:06:01.35,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,to tend to Saint Hakushin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.92,0:06:04.11,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Saint Hakushin?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.89,0:06:08.29,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,He was a great, wise priest who\nlived over a hundred years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.46,0:06:17.09,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Pure is impure.\NImpure is pure.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.03,0:06:25.34,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Good is evil.\NEvil is good.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.84,0:06:25.87,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}To live is to die. To die is to live.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.87,0:06:28.64,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}To live is to die. To die is to live.{\i0}\NHe became a living Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.64,0:06:28.74,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}To live is to die. To die is to live.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.74,0:06:31.01,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}To live is to die. To die is to live.{\i0}\nand is enshrined in a\ntemple on the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.01,0:06:32.71,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}To live is to die. To die is to live.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.71,0:06:33.72,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}To live is to die. To die is to live.{\i0}\NA living Buddha?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.72,0:06:33.94,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,A living Buddha?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.88,0:06:36.75,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,It's called {\i1}sokushin-butsu.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.75,0:06:43.71,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,A priest of great virtue meditates\nand fasts until his body mummifies
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.79,0:06:45.26,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,and attains Nirvana.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.69,0:06:48.36,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,In other words,\na dried-up priest?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.76,0:06:50.36,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Watch what you say!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.70,0:06:53.67,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,You said your father\nhasn't returned home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.00,0:06:56.23,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Yes, it's been over\ntwo weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.51,0:06:58.87,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,A strange light fell on\nthe island.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.14,0:06:59.77,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.14,0:07:02.51,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Father was concerned\nabout the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.78,0:07:04.18,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Strange light?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.51,0:07:06.85,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Probably Naraku.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.45,0:07:09.97,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Shintaro, it's impossible\nfor you alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.32,0:07:11.25,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sister....{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.82,0:07:16.22,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,But Father told me to take care\nof things if anything happened to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.49,0:07:19.09,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,The villagers said something\nabout a curse?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.60,0:07:22.86,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,The villagers are wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.20,0:07:25.60,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Father protected the village\nall his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.67,0:07:28.50,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,There has to be a reason for\nhis failure to return!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.67,0:07:32.30,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes....{\i0} We're worried about\nour father, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.67,0:07:35.11,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,And the villagers fear a curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.68,0:07:36.84,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,We're at a loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.18,0:07:38.70,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Let's go, Inuyasha.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.08,0:07:42.28,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yeah....{\i0} There's got to be something\nabout that sacred place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.48,0:07:44.38,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,You'll go? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.82,0:07:45.68,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.99,0:07:48.92,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,It's only natural for you\nto worry about your pa.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.62,0:07:50.45,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.96,0:07:53.43,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I'll guide you across\nthe lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.00,0:07:58.06,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,The island is always covered\nwith mist and can be dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.37,0:08:00.73,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Please take care of\nour younger brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.07,0:08:04.87,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Shintaro is the only male\nleft in our family.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.11,0:08:07.10,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,That must worry you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.71,0:08:12.58,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,If you'll agree, I can help you\nand your sisters bear some males.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.12,0:08:19.42,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Can we really entrust our\nbrother to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.89,0:08:23.36,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,No complaints, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.43,0:08:27.16,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Inuyasha! Don't threaten them!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.46,0:08:30.76,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. We just want to borrow\nyour boat for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.97,0:08:33.13,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,We'll return it!\NDon't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.67,0:08:40.83,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,It must be the sacred aura\nfrom Hijiri Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.11,0:08:43.63,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,It's so strong, even\NKirara can't transform.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.38,0:08:51.95,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}To live is to die.\NTo die is to live.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.69,0:08:56.15,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Saint Hakushin\nbeneath the earth{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.83,0:09:00.49,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mt. Hakurei will return to Hijiri.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.70,0:09:03.96,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.30,0:09:07.39,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,It's a children's song that's been sung\naround this region for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.70,0:09:12.30,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,From the time he was alive,\NSaint Hakushin had amazing spiritual powers
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.37,0:09:15.04,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,and saved many people\nof this region.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.31,0:09:18.61,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,There! You can see Mt. Hakurei.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.35,0:09:22.28,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,At the base is a place\nof purification.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.78,0:09:24.27,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Place of Purification?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.72,0:09:26.78,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,It's a temple built\nby the wise one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.16,0:09:31.02,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,If you pray there, any and all sins\nare absolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.83,0:09:34.80,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mt. Hakurei again?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.93,0:09:41.30,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Listen....{\i0} I wonder who put up\nthe barrier around Mt. Hakurei.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.74,0:09:48.40,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,You're right. Someone had to\nput up the barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.18,0:09:54.77,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,But it's the total opposite of the\nkind of barrier Naraku would use.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.52,0:10:03.01,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}It seems as if a holy person\nput up the barrier, but why?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.36,0:10:07.42,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Hijiri Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.96,0:10:10.86,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Be careful. There are\ncraggy rocks everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.10,0:10:12.76,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,If the boat hits against\none of these {\i1}rocks....{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.54,0:10:14.16,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.50,0:10:16.13,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Arghh!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.47,0:10:17.67,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Say that sooner!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.21,0:10:20.64,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Geez! This was a borrowed boat!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.71,0:10:23.61,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Shaddup! Keep complaining\nand I'll leave you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.88,0:10:25.94,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I can't swim.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.15,0:10:28.64,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Shippo, I can't see in front of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.42,0:10:30.91,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh? This {\i1}is....{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.79,0:10:35.35,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Are you all right, Miroku?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.59,0:10:38.99,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,You saved me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.67,0:10:46.63,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,This {\i1}is....{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.30,0:10:49.50,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,The same barrier as Mt. {\i1}Hakurei....{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.27,0:10:52.00,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Although not as strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.52,0:11:02.78,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.19,0:11:05.48,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,These {\i1}flowers....{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.09,0:11:08.45,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,smell the same as\NNaraku's demon puppet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.06,0:11:12.86,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,There never used to be\nflowers like these.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.60,0:11:18.96,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Are you all right, Shippo?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.37,0:11:20.27,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yeah....{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.24,0:11:22.86,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,The scent is overpowering\NKirara, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.71,0:11:27.07,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is all too convenient...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.14,0:11:30.58,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why did that Naraku...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.85,0:11:37.88,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}create a damn puppet just\nto help the Band of Seven escape?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.72,0:11:44.95,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}And then leaving this strong\nscent of the flowers...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.36,0:11:49.42,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's like I was lured to these\nsacred grounds by it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.40,0:11:55.16,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.80,0:11:57.33,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,The Wise One's temple!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.54,0:12:01.01,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's destroyed! But why...?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.48,0:12:01.97,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Aghh!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.62,0:12:10.28,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Father's {\i1}clothing....{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.35,0:12:12.18,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.75,0:12:14.09,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,F-Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.16,0:12:18.39,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,His father came to the\nisland two weeks ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.89,0:12:21.69,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,It's too soon to turn\ninto bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.90,0:12:24.06,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Could it have been\NNaraku's demons?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.27,0:12:26.86,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I'm sure of it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.34,0:12:29.03,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.17,0:12:33.14,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,This island has the temple {\i1}and....{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.58,0:12:34.10,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.25,0:12:39.58,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I sense a Shikon Jewel shard!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.18,0:12:48.52,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Damn! About time!\NMaking me wait so long in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.59,0:12:52.12,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.43,0:12:57.26,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,This place makes even a human\nlike me feel sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.63,0:13:01.03,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,It must be even more\ntrying for a half-demon, Inuyasha!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.60,0:13:02.33,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Bankotsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.20,0:13:06.00,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Damn, it was a trap!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.21,0:13:09.77,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Did you do this,\NBankotsu?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.91,0:13:12.14,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Don't look at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.88,0:13:15.78,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I was only told to wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.32,0:13:20.69,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Be careful, Inuyasha!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.22,0:13:23.62,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Bankotsu's halberd has\NSacred Jewel shards in it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.33,0:13:29.73,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,It got scarred during\nour little match the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.13,0:13:32.16,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,So I used them to mend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.47,0:13:37.63,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Let's do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.01,0:13:42.03,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,This time,\NI'll cut you to pieces!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.55,0:13:49.81,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,That's my line!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.53,0:14:04.33,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Inuyasha is on the defensive!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.97,0:14:07.43,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Because of the Sacred Jewel shards\nin Bankotsu's halberd.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.67,0:14:11.20,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.51,0:14:13.74,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I'm sick of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.14,0:14:15.44,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Wind Scar!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.42,0:14:31.45,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}W-What....?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.63,0:14:35.96,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,He couldn't invoke the Wind Scar?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.66,0:14:40.66,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,No wonder he told me to\nfight you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.51,0:14:45.06,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.18,0:14:48.80,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Why can't he use the Wind Scar?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.24,0:14:53.54,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Tetsusaiga's demonic power is\nbeing purified by Hijiri Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.68,0:14:54.27,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.12,0:14:58.85,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Furthermore, no matter how\nevil Bankotsu's spirit may be,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.05,0:15:00.28,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,he was still a mere human.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.16,0:15:03.12,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Compared to Inuyasha in whom\ncourses demon blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.19,0:15:05.56,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,the effect of Hijiri Island on Bankotsu\nis minimal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.46,0:15:10.59,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Inuyasha, you're much weaker\nthan when we last fought.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.23,0:15:14.20,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Now hurry up and die!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.54,0:15:18.56,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I want to get off this uncomfortable\nisland as soon as I can!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.92,0:15:35.19,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,There has to be someone\nputting up this purifying barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.79,0:15:40.32,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Just as I thought...\NIt's over there.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.27,0:15:47.89,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.54,0:15:56.31,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Shintaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.98,0:16:04.11,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Saint Hakushin!\NPlease help Inuyasha!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.49,0:16:10.18,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,This {\i1}is....{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.49,0:16:11.19,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Father's....{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.83,0:16:14.66,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Shintaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.40,0:16:19.37,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Saint Hakushin isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.30,0:16:21.13,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Not here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.57,0:16:23.50,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,He was enshrined in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.68,0:16:28.64,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}What's going on?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.48,0:16:32.84,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Does this mean Naraku\nattacked this island to...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.48,0:16:39.25,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Miroku, Saint Hakukshin's\nmummy is gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.55,0:16:41.04,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Naraku may've stolen it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.42,0:16:45.83,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Gone? Then it wasn't\NSaint Hakushin {\i1}who....?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.60,0:16:54.00,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Then who is putting up this\nsacred barrier on Hijiri Island?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.08,0:17:02.41,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Yahh!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.78,0:17:08.18,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Arghh!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.49,0:17:13.25,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Inuyasha!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.62,0:17:15.45,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.29,0:17:20.09,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Miroku....{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.73,0:17:27.19,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I thought Saint Hakushin was\nputting up this barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.47,0:17:29.99,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,What're you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.24,0:17:33.11,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,The Saint was someone\nwho saved people!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.27,0:17:34.76,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Why would he put up\na barrier?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.84,0:17:37.87,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,The strange light you and\nyour father saw
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.95,0:17:39.64,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,was a demon named Naraku.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.35,0:17:41.08,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Naraku?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.82,0:17:46.88,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Your father fought Naraku and tried\nto protect the Saint.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.28,0:18:18.18,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Saint Hakushin!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.26,0:18:29.70,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,So then....that skeleton was\nmy father.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.10,0:18:34.80,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Naraku was planning to use\NSaint Hakushin's spiritual power.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.80,0:18:39.24,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Your father tried to stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.98,0:18:42.84,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,That is the duty of\nthe village headman.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.05,0:18:46.64,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Father didn't die because\nhe was cursed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.12,0:18:48.14,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.18,0:18:49.95,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.15,0:18:57.25,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Then where is\NSaint Hakushin's mummy?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.36,0:19:00.05,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Who put up this barrier?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.90,0:19:05.52,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.03,0:19:08.00,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,One more time!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.27,0:19:13.97,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,This is the end for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.95,0:19:24.04,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Inuyasha, hang on a bit longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.96,0:19:29.72,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,If I can find the core\nof the {\i1}barrier....{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.29,0:19:32.09,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Shippo, lend me your powers!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.23,0:19:33.85,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.97,0:19:43.44,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Shippo's demonic powers which\NI transferred to the sutra charms{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.50,0:19:44.77,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}should produce a reaction!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.24,0:19:49.17,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,They've been purified!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.31,0:19:50.00,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,It's over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.36,0:20:07.23,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,That's an altar ornament\NSaint Hakushin always used!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.53,0:20:08.50,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,This is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.67,0:20:16.83,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I'll use this staff that Saint Hakushin\nonce owned. We'll try together!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.10,0:20:18.07,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Miroku....{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.11,0:20:23.34,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Let's try.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.65,0:20:35.14,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Give me strength, Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.49,0:21:11.08,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,The flowers have disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.80,0:21:19.13,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Wind Scar is back!\NThe barrier is broken!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.50,0:21:22.97,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,This is what created\nthe barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.37,0:21:26.00,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,But this vajra was\nlocked up in the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.91,0:21:31.68,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Does this mean that Saint Hakushin is\nlending his powers to Naraku?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.68,0:21:38.91,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Don't think this'll save you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.35,0:21:45.09,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,With the barrier gone,\NI'm feeling much stronger, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.60,0:21:50.06,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,That disgusting barrier is finally gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.83,0:21:55.80,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,So let's settle this\nonce and for all, Inuyasha!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.38,0:23:47.54,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Take this! Dragon Thunder!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.95,0:23:49.25,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Multiple lightning bolts!?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.45,0:23:51.75,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Damn you!\NInvolving Kagome and the others!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.09,0:23:54.68,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,There's nothing unfair\nin war!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.86,0:23:57.05,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I'll kill you if it kills me, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.73,0:23:59.39,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Inuyasha fights Bankotsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.03,0:24:03.62,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,During their battle, Saint Hakushin's\npower saves Bankotsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.27,0:24:08.53,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Next on Inuyasha:\N"The Sacred Vajra\nand the Mystery of the Living Buddha"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.80,0:24:11.90,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Could Saint Hakushin be\nhelping Bankotsu?!
